Dan Cunningham (London)

12:02 PM

@SamanyuChopra follow same steps above and make sure under Additional Features "Live Events" is enabled

Samanyu Chopra (New Delhi)

12:02 PM

Okay

Dan Cunningham (London)

12:04 PM

ideal set up is:
a. one laptop, on the Hangout, with webcam pointed at your big screen, so it is properly focused and exposure is good, with mic muted
b. one laptop, on the Hangout, with webcam pointed at person speaking, with mic turned on (you may leave this one connected to Spreecast too)

Each team presenting then just plugs their laptop into your projector for their live demo

Samanyu Chopra (New Delhi)

12:05 PM

I have invited you

Dan Cunningham (London)

12:05 PM

alternative set up is:
a. one laptop, on the Hangout, with webcam pointed at your big screen, so it is properly focused and exposure is good, with mic muted
b. invite each presenting team to the Hangout and they can share their screen to get an event better quality of live demo

The limitation of this set up is only 10 people can be invited to the hangout, and it's a little bit more faffing, but if you can make it work, it's better!

Reuben Katz (Geeklist)

12:06 PM

Dan... that limitation isn't a problem as everyone gets invited to watch live on youtube

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

Pedro Baptista Afonso (Lisbon)

1:44 AM

hey guys! update on Partner Swag!
@all we didn't send the API Partner Swag email out yet, here are the details that you can share:
To help you get off to a flying start at #hack4good 0.5 our wonderful partners have some special gifts for you!

These are all great tools to help you prototype, develop and launch fast during the 48-hours!

Rackspace
6 months of Cloud Hosting ($50/month value) for everyone
Go to http://developer.rackspace.com/devtrial
Use code #rackspace-dev

Gandi.net
Gandi.net is providing free domain names for the winning teams
Winners should contact thomas@gandi.net

Proto.io
Silly fast mobile prototyping!
2-month trial account for all #hack4good participants
Sign up for free 15-day trial at http://proto.io/en/signup/
Activate “Pro” subscription using code hack4good-2m-comp

Hull
Social infrastructure for modern apps. Hull is a set of open engagement APIs that let you build user login and authentication, activity feeds, messaging, likes, ratings, comments and more into your apps in minutes.
Hull is free to get started with! Sign up at http://hull.io/pricing
ALSO: to support volume as projects launch and grow, Hull are giving the winning team in each location 12 months x Silver plan ($1188 value), and the runners up 6 months x Silver plan ($594 value)!

Lob
Lob provides the easiest way to integrate print & mail solutions into your business and applications. Think Amazon Web Services, Twilio, or Stripe for printing & mailing.
As part of this weekend’s swag pack, you get $20 in credits from Lob.com
Your unique promo code is: *|LOBCODE|*
To redeem your promo code, please visit http://www.lob.com/credits. For new users, you must first sign up and then revisit the link.

WhiteSpell
Whitespell is a lightweight, independent solution to build powerful, dynamic, intelligent, and scalable web-and mobile applications in HTML5.
Whitespell will be exclusively launched for you to use at #hack4good to build your own ultra-responsive web/mobile apps!
Check out Pim’s WhiteSpell demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact PimdeWitte in Hipchat.

Resin.io
Resin.io is javascript on your devices, as simple as 'git push'
Resin.io will be launching their API at #hack4good for up to 10 teams to work with!
Check out Alexandros’s Resin.io demo spreecast and if you want to find out more and try it out, contact AlexandrosMarinos in Hipchat.

Don’t forget we also have public and private hosted git repos you can use at git.geekli.st

Questions? Need support? All the API partners have a chat room set up in Hipchat and will be there to support you! (if you haven’t yet done it, create your Hack4good Hipchat account)

A huge thank you to: Vyjayanthi at Rackspace, Thomas at Gandi.net, Alexis at Proto.io, Stefan & Stefan at Hull.io, Dan at Lob.com, Pim at WhiteSpell and Alexandros at Resin.io for partnering with Geeklist to support the development of projects for social good!

CREATE TABLE person (
  id smallint(5) unsigned NOT NULL auto_increment,
  name varchar(30),
  email varchar(30),
  PRIMARY KEY (id),
  KEY idx_email (email)
) ENGINE=InnoDB;

CREATE TABLE shoe (
  ref int(10) unsigned NOT NULL auto_increment,
  personid smallint(5) unsigned NOT NULL,
  img blob,
  gender char(10),
  size char(10),
  type char(10),
  org char(30),
  local char(40),
  PRIMARY KEY (ref)
) ENGINE=InnoDB;

CREATE TABLE person (
    -> id smallint(5) unsigned NOT NULL auto_increment,
    -> name varchar(30),
    -> email varchar(30),
    -> PRIMARY KEY (id),
    -> KEY idx_email (email)
    -> ) ENGINE=InnoDB;

Tiago Correia (Lisbon)

3:14 AM

CREATE TABLE shoe (
    -> ref int(10) unsigned NOT NULL auto_increment,
    -> personid smallint(5) unsigned NOT NULL,
    -> img blob,
    -> gender char(10),
    -> size char(10),
    -> type char(10),
    -> org char(30),
    -> local char(40),
    -> PRIMARY KEY (ref)
    -> ) ENGINE=InnoDB;

ALTER TABLE shoe
    -> ADD CONSTRAINT FK_shoe
    -> FOREIGN KEY (personid) REFERENCES person(id)
    -> ON UPDATE CASCADE
    -> ON DELETE CASCADE;
